  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Measuring hemodynamic parameters in ventilated patients is important yet still complicated
      to perform. Inert gas rebreathing (IGR) showed promising results when being compared to
      other invasive as well as non-invasive techniques for the measurement of cardiac output. The
      aim of our study is to evaluate the feasibility of IGR in ventilated patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
